window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p><i>Psychology of...Horror Villains, Survivors, and Victims</i> poses this question: If our favorite characters were real, what would their psychological disorder be? Could they have been helped? What type of treatments would they have received? Why were some people survivors, and why did others become victims?</p> <p>S.L. Yarbrough uses her masters degree in applied behavioral science with an emphasis in psychology and criminal justice to analyze each one. If you love hearing about criminal psychology, or are a student majoring in psychology, or find true-crime stories fascinating, and, of course, are a fan of horror, then you will enjoy<i> Psychology of...Horror Villains, Survivors, and Victims</i>, the first in an extensive series looking at all genres.</p>"; 
